BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:49cca0ec183445d91b51494cb716e993
SUMMARY:SmashingConf Amsterdam 2026
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260413
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260416
LOCATION:Pathé Tuschinski, Amsterdam, the Netherlands
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://smashingconf.com/amsterdam-2026/\nA 4-day Smashing Conference on UX and front-end for designers, UI engineers, and UX professionals. The event includes 2 conference days with a single track featuring 12 speakers and 2 workshop days with 6 practical, deep-dive workshops. Topics covered include Design Systems, accessibility, Figma, UX writing, modern CSS, AI, leadership, data visualization, and human-centered interfaces, ranging from research to CSS and interface design. The conference focuses on real-world problems and solutions, offering practical and actionable insights through interactive sessions. It's an inclusive event for 550 attendees, providing networking opportunities, job opportunities, and side activities like morning runs, yoga, boat tours, and photo walks.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:b4f26d70c292c02f7efc16cdd0fca6f4
SUMMARY:Prompt:UX
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260121
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260122
LOCATION:Berlin, Germany
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://condens.io/guides/ux-conference-guide-2026/\nThe prompt:UX Conference focuses on the intersection of artificial intelligence and user experience design, gathering designers, researchers, and product managers to explore how AI is reshaping UX and how to prepare strategies, tools, and workflows accordingly. Expect engaging keynotes from industry leaders, hands-on workshops, case studies, and a dedicated networking reception, all aimed at helping your team integrate AI into UX in meaningful, future-ready ways. If you’re looking to stay at the forefront of AI-powered UX design and research, this conference offers the insights, practical learning, and connections to make that happen.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
